### Problem Description

Synthetic source produces wrong documents in case of a field having both native and ignored source

### Steps to Reproduce

```
PUT /my_index
{
  "settings": {
    "index": {
      "sort.field": "name", 
      "sort.order": "asc"  
    }
  },
  "mappings": {
    "_source": { "mode": "synthetic" },
    "dynamic": "runtime",
    "properties": {
      "name": {
        "type": "keyword"
      },
      "foo": {
        "type": "keyword",
        "store": true
      }
    }
  }
}

POST my_index/_bulk?refresh
{ "create": {} }
{ "name": "a", "foo": [null, "hello_from_the_other_side"] }
{ "create": {} }
{ "name": "b", "foo": null }

POST my_index/_search
```

Produces:
```
"hits": [
    {
        "_index": "my_index",
        "_id": "Ihrhf5EBLJ3X8EiEoe8f",
        "_score": 1,
        "_source": {
            "foo": [
                null,
                "hello_from_the_other_side"
            ],
            "name": "a"
        }
    },
    {
        "_index": "my_index",
        "_id": "Ixrhf5EBLJ3X8EiEoe8g",
        "_score": 1,
        "_source": {
            "foo": "hello_from_the_other_side",  <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<
            "name": "b"
        }
    }
]
```

